main-menu:
[low, sultry, smoke-curling] Mmm. Well hello there, stranger. [half-smile, knowing] You picked up my phone. That means you're either lost... [long beat, unhurried] ...or exactly where you're supposed to be. [husky, low chuckle] Out here, it's usually both.
[hushed, almost a whisper] Now, if you already know my numbers... [sly, lips-curled] ...well. You know what to do.
[velvet, commanding but unhurried] But if this is the first time you've called, [slow, sultry] these are your options.
[low, deliberate] Press 1, and I'll ring you through to whoever's picking up on the other end. [wry, half-laughing] Could be anyone, darling. That's the fun of it.
[low, amused, private] Press 2 if you want to hear what's been whispered in my ear — messages left by the ones who came before you.
[intimate, leaning in, almost touching the mic] And press 3 if you've got something to say yourself. [low, private, trailing off] Everyone shares their secrets with me.
[soft, smoky, drawn-out] Whatever brought you to this phone... [long pause] ...the desert sent you here for a reason.
[warm, low, half-dismissive] Go on now. Make your selection.

main-menu-short:
[dry, arch] Well. Seems you need a little help finding your way. [low, a little amused] Press 1 to ring the other line. [wry] Could be anyone, darling. Could be fun. [flat, sultry] Press 2 for messages left by the ones who came before you. [cool, half-smiling] Press 3 to leave a message of your own. [low, private, trailing off] Everyone has secrets to share. [warm, dry] Tick tock, sugar... [beat] time to choose.

Invalid:
1. [dry, flat] Darling, that's not one of the numbers I mentioned. [low, sultry] Or one of the ones I don't say out loud. [beat] Try again.
2. [low, amused] Mmm, no. [wry] One, two, or three — [beat, low, teasing] there could be more. [playful] I'll never tell. [low] But that wasn't any of them.
3. cool, arch] Careful now — a girl could take that personally. [beat, dry] One, two, three. [low, sly] Some things I keep to myself. [beat, playful] That wasn't one of them, though.
4. [low, tired-but-warm] Not it, darling. [beat] One, two, three — that's what I hand out. [low, teasing] The rest is just for me to know. [beat] But that wasn't one of those, was it.
5. [low, playful, slow] Wrong number, stranger. [beat, low, teasing] There's more than three, if you're clever enough to find them. [low] That wasn't it, though. [beat] Try again.
6. [flat, clipped] That's not a choice. [dry, pointed] One, two, three. [beat, low, sly] There might be a few I've never mentioned. [flat, playful] but that wasn't one of them. [beat] Try again darling.

vm-record_message:
[matter-of-fact] Say what you need to say after the tone, [sultry, quick] i'm listening and so is the desert, [matter-of-fact, gentle] you've got 60 seconds. [low] When you're done, just stop talking or press any key, [private, sexy] and it will be mine to keep, darling.

vm-saved:
[warm, low] Got it, stranger. [beat, soft] Safe with me now.

vm-no_more_messages:
[low, a little wistful] That's all of them, darling [beat] for now.
[warm, dry] Come back later. Someone's always got something to say eventually. [beat, playful] Or... you could leave one now. [low, warm] Just a thought sugar.

disco-raise:
[low, sly, building energy] Oh-ho. Now that's a number I didn't expect tonight.
[playful, a little breathless] Go on... [beat] look up, darling.
[warm, building excitement] The desert's about to get a little brighter. [beat, delighted] Don't say I never gave you anything.

disco-already-up:
[beat, sultry] The ball's up, darling — it's been spinning this whole time, waiting on you to notice.
[sly, low] What more do you want from me, hm? [beat, jokingly] Fireworks? [playful] I don't do fireworks.
[warm, low, building] But this— [beat] this is mine. All that light, just for you. [sultry, slow] So what's it going to be, darling?
[low, warm, inviting] Shall we dance?

disco-lower:
[low, wistful, a little sly] Mmm. All good things, darling. [beat] Even mine.
[soft, low] Watch — [beat, slow] she's coming back down to earth.
[warm, dry, affectionate] Don't look so heartbroken. [beat, teasing] She'll rise again for the right number.

disco-already-down:
[low, wry, amused] Mmm, sugar, look again. [beat] She's already tucked in for the night.
[dry, playful] No light to give you right now. [beat, low, teasing] Come back when there's something worth looking up for.

disco-stop:
[low, delighted, sly] Ohhh. Look at you. [beat, amused] Found something.
[playful, teasing] Shame it doesn't do a thing, hm? [beat, warm, wry] Not every secret's got a prize behind it, darling.
[low, sultry, dismissive] Some things I just keep... because I can. [beat] Try another.

no-answer:
[low, wry, amused] Mmm. Rang and rang, darling. [beat] Out there in the dark, somewhere — nobody's picking up.
[low, wistful] Could be they're dancing. [beat, playful] Could be they wandered off with someone more interesting than a ringing phone. [dry] Out here, that happens more than you'd think.
[warm, low] Either way — [beat] that line's gone quiet on me tonight.
[warm, dry, affectionate] Try again later, sugar. [beat, teasing] Or leave a little something behind for whoever it is. [low, private] They'll come back to it. They always do.

========================================================================
PROMPT FILES — what to record and what plays each
========================================================================

Custom prompts — your voice — live in prompts/ as 8 kHz mono WAV (converted from
the uploaded MP3s). All of these are now wired into the config:
  main-menu.wav            The "Main Menu" script. Played at 700; digits are
                           collected over it (barge-in).
  main-menu-short.wav      The "Short Menu" script. NOTE: not used by the current
                           dialplan (only main-menu.wav is). Kept for future use.
  invalid-entry-1..6.wav   Your six "Invalid" scripts. One is played at random on
                           a wrong entry (scripts/bella-messages invalid-prompt).
  vm-record_message.wav    Option 3 "leave a message" — spoken before the beep.
  vm-saved.wav             Played after a message is recorded.
  vm-no_more_messages.wav  Option 2 — "no messages" and end-of-messages.
  no-answer.wav            Option 1 — played when the other line does not answer.
  disco-raise.wav          911 when the ball is down/unknown — spoken as it raises.
  disco-already-up.wav     911 when the ball is already up (does not move).
  disco-lower.wav          411 when the ball is up/unknown — spoken as it lowers.
  disco-already-down.wav   411 when the ball is already down (does not move).
  disco-stop.wav           #  stop — spoken when stopping the ball.

Caller messages — auto-generated, do NOT record:
  recordings/messages/msg_<timestamp>_<uuid>.wav
      A message left by a caller (option 3). The newest 10 are played back
      (option 2), oldest-first; older messages are kept on disk and only pruned
      when free space runs low. Managed by scripts/bella-messages.

Still using generated / stock audio:
  (beep tone)                            tone_stream (not a file) — the record-start beep.
  ivr/ivr-that_was_an_invalid_entry.wav  stock — intercom fallback for an unexpected SIP user.

Notes:
  - Custom prompts live in prompts/ (tracked in git). The .mp3 uploads are kept
    as source; FreeSWITCH plays the .wav (mod_sndfile has no MP3 support).
  - For the narrowband ATA path, prompts are 8 kHz mono WAV.
